
Relational database is a physical representation of a business system.
It is a persistent store of information outside of the application.

SQL - industry-standard language for creating and interacting with a relational database.

Most languages (Java, PHP, etc) have the capability to issue SQL statements to a relational database.
There are number of tools to issue SQL statements (ex., SQL Developer, SQL*Plus)

SQL:
DDL (Data Definition Language):
  - CREATE
  - ALTER
  - DROP
  - RENAME
  - TRUNCATE
  - GRANT
  - REVOKE
  - FLASHBACK
  - PURGE
  - COMMENT
  - ANALYZE. AUDIT, ASSOCIATE STATISTICS, DIASSOCIATE, NOAUDIT

DML (Data Manipulation languge)
  - SELECT
  - INSERT
  - UPDATE
  - DELETE 
  - MERGE
  - CALL, LOCK TABLE, EXPLAIN PLAN

TCL (Transaction Control Langiage)
  - COMMIT
  - ROLLBACK  SAVEPOINT
  - SET TRANSACTION, SET CONSTRAINT

Session Cotrol Statements (ALTER SESSION, SET ROLE)
System Control Statements (ALTER SYSTEM)
Embeded SQL Statements (Any DML, DDL, ot TCL that is integrated into a third-generation language (3GL)





